summary: Student with a B.S. in Interdisciplinary Social Science (minor in Conflict Analysis and Trauma Studies) from Kansas State University (2015). Over 8.5 years in the US Army with extensive experience in executive administrative duties, training and development, personnel information management, counseling and mentorship, conflict resolution, general office operations, and travel coordination. Proven ability to develop training modules and coordinate ceremonies; proficient in Microsoft Office; strong interpersonal and organizational skills.

experience.title: Student
experience.description: Diligently maintained living environment for three individuals and two pets while completing a Bachelors of Science through distance learning; provided three nutritional meals daily; responsible for the care and well-being of one child.

experience.title: Executive Administrative Assistant
experience.description: Essential member of the Army communications maintenance team; performed field and sustainment maintenance on avionic navigation flight control systems; maintained, tested and repaired communication equipment; installed and repaired circuits and wiring; calibrated and aligned equipment; tested and isolated faulty assemblies; replaced parts and interconnect components on a semiautomatic telephone switchboard.

experience.title: Executive Administrative Assistant Senior Commander
experience.description: Coordinated and scheduled training visits, briefings, appointments, correspondences and travel arrangements for the 1st Infantry Division Deputy Commanding General/Senior Commander. Demonstrated strong people skills and ability to multi-task in fast-paced environments; managed communications and scheduling.

experience.title: S3 Operations Noncommissioned Officer
experience.description: Supervised, trained and led up to 5 soldiers daily; created and maintained brigade operation orders; delegated tasks to subordinate units; maintained flight logs and individual flight records.

experience.title: Executive Administrative Assistant
experience.description: Executive Administrative Assistant to the Division Command Sergeant Major; facilitated flow of information to/from the Division Command Sergeant Major, subordinate Command Sergeants Major and Sergeants Major; coordinated and scheduled training visits, briefings, appointments, correspondences and travel arrangements; oversaw over 15 boards and 27 award ceremonies; provided oversight to evaluation reports, awards, and administrative matters; supervised and mentored 2 Soldiers.

experience.title: Administrative Assistant
experience.description: Administrative assistant for brigade command group; instructor for brigade junior leader course; mentored and developed 54 students; developed a risk management lesson adopted as brigade standard; coordinated over 25 air and ground travel arrangements for the Brigade Command Sergeant Major.

experience.title: Orderly Room Clerk
experience.description: Developed and utilized a company database to efficiently maintain personnel records for 320 personnel and family readiness rosters; provided training, health, welfare, and technical guidance to personnel.

experience.title: Cashier/Copy Center
experience.description: Maintained stock of resale items; operated pricing and electronic checkout systems; assisted customers; counted cash and prepared accountability reports; managed self-checkout registers and cash handling.

education.degree: Bachelor of Science in Interdisciplinary Social Science (Minor in Conflict Analysis and Trauma Studies)
